text.__SUMMARY__: Syzygium xerampelinum, known as the Mulgrave satinash, is a rare rainforest tree of tropical Queensland, Australia. The bark and fruit are similar to the often cultivated magenta cherry.
text.References: Walter, K.S.; Gillett, H.J.; Centre, W.C.M.; Nature, I.U.f.C.o.; Commission, N.R.S.S. (1998). 1997 IUCN Red List of Threatened Plants. IUCN - The World Conservation Union. ISBN 9782831703282.
